## 3. Technical & System Architecture

### 3.1 Tech Stack

* **Client Framework:** Vite + Modern Vanilla JavaScript ES6 Modules
* **3D Rendering Pipeline:** Three.js (WebGL Renderer)
* **Physics Simulation Engine:** Cannon-es (Rigid body contact solvers & collision tracking)
* **Real-time Networking:** Socket.IO Client / Express Server
* **Version Control:** Git / GitHub (Feature-branch workflow)

### 3.2 Network Synchronization & Room Architecture

* **Isolated Multi-Room Gateway:** The backend server uses Socket.IO namespaces to partition players into private room channels (`rooms[roomCode]`) using generated 4-character alphanumeric session keys (e.g., `A4X9`).
* **State Broadcast Loop:** Updates position ($\vec{P}$), camera rotation ($\vec{R}$), active camouflage state, and assigned player role (`Hunter` vs. `Runner`) across room members at $60\text{ Hz}$.
* **Garbage Collection:** Server automatically purges empty room objects upon member disconnect to prevent memory leaks.

